'''''Republic Commando: Hard Contact''''' is a 293-page tie-in novel to the [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Republic Commando]]'' and the first novel in the [[Republic Commando|''Republic Commando'' series]]. The book, written by [[Karen Traviss]] and published by [[Del Rey]] on [[October]] [[October 26|26]], [[2004]], is set in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]] during the [[Rise of the Empire era]]. It tells the story of a [[Omega Squad|squad]] of [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commandos]] on a mission to destroy a [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] [[Bioweapon/Legends|bioweapons]] lab on the [[Planet/Legends|world]] of [[Qiilura/Legends|Qiilura]]. The commandos ([[Niner Skirata|Niner]], [[Fi Skirata|Fi]], [[Atin Skirata|Atin]], and [[Darman Skirata|Darman]]) are aided by the [[Gurlanin]]s [[Jinart]] and [[Valaqil]], along with an inexperienced [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] named [[Etain Tur-Mukan]] and a Weequay named Guta-Nay.

==Publisher's summary==
'''As the Clone Wars rage, victory or defeat lies in the hands of elite squads that take on the toughest assignments in the galaxy&mdash;stone-cold soldiers who go where no one else would, to do what no one else could&hellip;.'''<ref name="Hard Contact" />

''On a mission to sabotage a nanovirus research facility on a Separatist-held planet, four clone troopers operate under the very noses of their enemies. The commandos are outnumbered and outgunned, deep behind enemy lines with no backup&mdash;and working with strangers instead of trusted teammates. Matters don't improve when Darman, the squad's demolitions expert, gets cut off from the others during planetfall. Even Darman's apparent good luck in meeting a Jedi Padawan vanishes once she admits to her woeful inexperience.''<ref name="Hard Contact" />

''For the isolated clone commandos and stranded Jedi, a long, dangerous journey lies ahead, through hostile territory brimming with Trandoshan slavers, Separatists, and suspicious natives. A single misstep could mean discovery &hellip; and death. It's a virtual suicide mission for anyone&mdash;anyone except Republic Commandos.''<ref name="Hard Contact" />

==Plot summary==
{{Quote|No Sarge, ''that'' was endex.|Fi, on Qiilura after creating an asteroid belt out of a Separatist nanovirus research facility|<ref name="Hard Contact" />}}
Four [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commandos]]; [[Niner Skirata|Niner]], [[Darman Skirata|Darman]], [[Fi Skirata|Fi]] and [[Atin Skirata|Atin]]; are united for the first time to form [[Omega Squad]] after the rest of their old squads were killed early in the Clone Wars. Meanwhile on [[Qiilura/Legends|Qiilura]], [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Etain Tur-Mukan]] hides from the local warlord [[Ghez Hokan]]'s militia after her [[Jedi Master/Legends|master]] [[Kast Fulier]] was killed.<ref name="Hard Contact" />

Omega learns their mission is to destroy a [[Cloning/Legends|clone]]-killing nanovirus being developed by the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatists]] on Qiilura and abduct the project's head scientist, [[Ovolot Qail Uthan]]. Darman is injured and separated from the squad on insertion after attempting to salvage extra equipment from the crashing vehicle, and slowly moves toward the rendezvous point, killing several of Hokan's men on the way. Re-grouping is hindered as the ruling [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidians]] control all the planet's communications, leaving Omega only a 10-meter comm-range. Concerned by the Republic infiltration, Dr. Uthan commissions Hokan as a Separatist officer and reinforces the area with 100 [[B1-series battle droid/Legends|battle droids]] and extra officers including the very adept [[Hurati|Lieutenant Hurati]].<ref name="Hard Contact" />

With the assistance of two [[Gurlanin]]s named [[Jinart]] and [[Valaqil]], Darman meets up with Etain and the two move on to a safehouse. After being sold out by the locals, they move on to rendezvous with the rest of Omega. Darman teaches Etain much about combat and leadership and the two begin to develop a bond. The rest of Omega Squad steal a large quantity of charges from a nearby gem mine and Niner commandeers an excavation droid to transport the charges to the ground station supporting the Neimoidians' communications and destroy it. While taking the explosives Omega also captures a Weequay named [[Guta-Nay]] who used to work for Hokan and they learn much about the facility. Free to communicate, Omega Squad, Etain and Jinart meet and prepare their attack on the facility.<ref name="Hard Contact" />

Jinart places a detonator in the cellar of [[Lik Ankkit]]'s mansion where most of the droids are garrisoned, leaving the nanovirus facility with little defense. The squad moves to the facility, where Niner, Fi and Etain set up an [[E-Web heavy repeating blaster/Legends|E-Web heavy repeating blaster]] for covering fire. Jinart helps Darman and Atin infiltrate the heavily armored facility through the surrounding [[gdan]] burrows. The two commandos blow their way into the facility initiating a lockdown and trapping Hokan and his officers, place implosion devices to destroy the virus and capture Uthan, leaving through the burrows. Hurati manages to override the lockdown and he escapes with Hokan. As Darman, Atin and Etain head towards the [[Low Altitude Assault Transport/infantry/Legends|LAAT/i]] for extraction, Hurati shoots Atin with a [[Verpine shatter gun]] seriously wounding him and Uthan, but Darman kills Hurati by shooting him in the head. Niner and Fi meet Hokan, and Niner lures him by pretending to be injured. Etain sees Hokan and kills him while searching for the two commandos by decapitating him with her lightsaber; and with that, she collects her dead master's lightsaber from Hokan's headless corpse, who happened to have the lightsaber. Unfortunately, Etain realized that she is getting attached to the Omega squad, because she never wanted to hear their screams again. Omega Squad are extracted, and Etain decides to stay on Qiilura with [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Arligan Zey]], primarily to prevent the attachment she is developing toward Darman.<ref name="Hard Contact" />

{{Plot}}

==Continuity==
''Hard Contact'' was the first of four [[Republic Commando|Republic Commando novels]] inspired by the [[Star Wars: Republic Commando|videogame]] of same name released by [[LucasArts]] in [[2005]]. The game focused on [[Delta Squad/Legends|Delta Squad]] – a team of specialized [[Clone commando/Legends|commandos]] that operate as a quartet behind enemy lines. Though the novel instead spotlighted [[Omega Squad]], the feel of the missions, the squad tactics involved, and the equipment used are all directly tied to the game.<ref name="ERC" />

